---
title: Buffalo-Spiced Crispy Chicken Cutlets with Monterey Jack, Mashed Potatoes, Buttery Broccoli & a Honey Drizzle
description: Are you the type of person who only goes to events because of the fact that buffalo wings may be present? We’re with you, and that’s why our chefs took the beloved dish from messy app to epic weeknight dinner. First, chicken is coated in a cheesy, Frank’s Red Hot spiced panko mixture. It’s roasted to juicy, crunchy perfection, then drizzled with creamy buffalo-style sauce. Oh, and did we mention there’s buttery roasted broccoli and sour cream and scallion mashed potatoes on the side?! Yeah, it’s safe to say this dish is a slam dunk/home run/total dinner goals.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/buffalo-spiced-crispy-chicken-cutlets-b2d4e0a0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/buffalo-spiced-crispy-chicken-cutlets-5e9dd11eddff362522313034-a3d344b5.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/buffalo-spiced-crispy-chicken-cutlets-5e9dd11eddff362522313034
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
